# Clean Architecture Standards

## Core Rules

1. **Dependencies point inward**: Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Interface
2. **Domain is pure**: NO framework imports (Spring, JPA, Hibernate, etc.)
3. **Interface segregation**: Consumer defines, producer implements
4. **Data transformation**: DTOs must not leak into Domain layer

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Do | Don't |
|-------|-----|-------|
| Domain | Entities, VOs, business rules | Import frameworks, use DI |
| Application | Use cases, commands | Business logic |
| Infrastructure | Persistence, external services | Define domain interfaces |
| Interface | Controllers, DTOs | Business logic |

## Correct vs Incorrect

```java
// ✅ Correct: Pure domain
public class Order {
    public void place() {
        if (status != DRAFT) throw new InvalidStateException();
        status = PLACED;
    }
}

// ❌ Incorrect: Domain has framework annotation
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;  // Forbidden!
@Component
public class Order { }
```

## Violations

| Symptom | Problem |
|---------|---------|
| `@Service` on domain class | Violates domain independence |
| JPA annotation in domain | Violates portability |
| Business logic in Controller | Violates separation |
| Entity with only getters/setters | Anemic domain model |

## Quick Check

```bash
# Domain should have no framework imports
grep -r "import org.springframework" src/domain/
grep -r "import jakarta.persistence" src/domain/
```
